I think the worse feeling on the planet is dwelling on the unsaid. Regretting what wasn’t spoken. I rather be frustrated or embarrassed with where the dominos fall instead of swell up with an opinion. I can’t bite my tongue when there’s bullshit, or when I feel someone needs to be told they’re dear to me, or if something isn’t working. Anyways… if you’re an asshole around me I’ll let you know. Sometimes I think I’m just bad at lying. 

#photodump #vinyl #dallas #nope

I feel like there’s a lot of music that focuses on love, hate, war, sex, drugs… but I feel London Grammar made a heart wrenching song “Wasting My Young Years” that really sent me into an existential crisis 9 years ago. I spent so much of my early 20s so stressed about living the most I could live… even if it be reckless or out of my comfort. I didn’t want to waste a day without experiencing something. I wanted to feel every type of love. This song really resonates with that feeling. Knowing time is fleeting, and trying to figure out if you’re doing it all right? What even is the right way to live? 
And now it’s 9 years later, and this song still rings true. I still have ambition to live fully. I still feel like myself 9 years ago when it came out in the sense of craving to experience everything. “Don’t you know it’s only fear. I wouldn’t worry you have your whole life. I’ve heard it takes some time to get it right.” I guess what I’m writing is I love a song that captures this feeling lyrically. I think if you’re lost and fear the years speeding by faster it’s a cathartic listen. It’s cool @recordstoredayus did this pressing. The vocals are so ghostly on the entire album, it’s beautiful. Actually makes me want to cry. @londongrammar 🙌

#londongrammar #music #rsd #rsd2023 #vinyl #records #recordshop

I never really wear white… I’m confident, but not wear white confident. 
However, this jumpsuit I got from Zara made me feel like a little curvy peach so I figured “fuck it”. I think I’ve spent my entire teen years and 20s being so concerned about my body in clothes… and like many women you hit your 30s and suddenly you regret the worry. You’ve always had a body to appreciate. I think any woman with curves, especially boobs, is on this pendulum of fashion. You want to look sexy, but not trashy. You want to show your curves, but not be fetishized. Idk about other women, but I often feel better about my body naked than in clothes. I’ll wake up loving my body until the pants are snug on. 
When I was 22 this photographer wanted to shoot me naked… artistically so… and I passed on it because I was weird about having nude photos exist of me without my control of them. It seemed too vulnerable to me. I was talking with a girlfriend the other day about it, and she asked if I regret not taking nude shots. Personally, I kind of love the mystery of my body… I like that if someone saw me fully naked it was skinny dipping after a bottle of wine, streaking as a dare, or intimately. A foggy memory. I think the only thing existing online is a photo I took of my pale ass from like 2 years ago when I couldn’t fit into my Halloween costume 😂 I’ve always had creative control over my nakedness. 
I root on every woman I know who dances on stage naked, I love it… and the body is a piece of artwork for the artists to showcase as they please. I love nudity. The more women own that the more power we have… physical expression is a freedom I think all deserve. Every woman is a baroque painting in my eyes. We are canvases and no one should every tell you how to paint yourself. There’s no shame in modesty or putting it all out there. I like my canvas as this weird mystery that’s suggestive, but never fully giving… it’s just how I am. 

 #jumpsuit #bodypositive #bodyrant #curves #redhead

I never really post any photos from my other job… it’s always records and my personal life on here. I work with Sharon Adams PR on events ranging from nonprofits to authors of books to preservation societies. I really enjoy it because there’s always a story/experience I can’t really compare to another. I always joke that it’s a double life between this and the record shop… maybe triple life with Ladylove now… oh and DJing too. They all don’t really collide, they’re separate worlds. I would lie to say at moments I don’t get overwhelmed with it all. I do doubles, and sometimes will find myself working online when I can’t sleep at 1am. I enjoy it all. I’ve loved the 5 years doing this because it’s given me perspective, I’ve met so many great people, and it’s given me excuses to buy fancy dresses. 
Anyways the other day I was going through photos taken by @dannycampbellphotography @tamytha & @rwythe and thought about how much of an experience it continues to be. I’m thankful for @sharonadamspr to be in my life and have given me this opportunity, if you need a PR agent who knows her stuff she’s a great boss. Just wanted to write about this part of my life so it exists somewhere. 

#dallasnonprofit #dallas #dfw #dallastexas #salum #bangs

As I get closer to Ladylove Lounge and Sound opening with David, Heather, and Jimmy, I’m enjoying any moments I get at Spinster Records. I’m not leaving Spinster, and of course it’s all sorts connected through David and I. You’ll see our staff hosting DJ nights there. 
I know this new spot will be taking all my time, and I won’t even be working my 8 year traditional Monday shift. I really love working at a record shop… it’s such a passion job. Even on a bad day, I love it. I hate when I’ve met people and they ask what I seriously want to do… as if working here has been a side gig onto something greater, but I honestly am happy with this. It’s simple and I have made a living off of it. I’ve had regulars who I’ve watched go from a date, to married, to having kids now. It’s insane, I’m 30 now and have been there since I was 21. It’s like being in a pleasant fishbowl. David and I worked Saturday morning together and of course it was a blast. We get along like we’ve lived many past lives together. It’s magic and I feel that energy will carry into whatever project we do. Just wanted to make this post to clarify I’ll be existing in as many jobs as I can because I love it all so much. Also Ladylove opens July 7th and I can’t wait to see everyone there 🧡

#vinyl #theclash #erykahbadu #dallas #bishoparts #oakcliff #records

I have a fond memory with Hunter where we were in Big Bend hiking 6 years ago. We had just gotten to know each other, and I asked him who is his favorite person for quotes. Without a hesitation he said “Yogi Berra… he said things like ‘It ain’t over ‘til it’s over’, and ‘Baseball is 90% mental. The other half is physical”. I was trying to connect and said “oh yeah! My favorite from him is ‘Aye Boo Boo! Let’s see what’s in the Pic-Nic Basket today!” Which made him laugh so hard he couldn’t breathe. That’s when I learned he loved baseball, and it was always a huge part of him… also I learned Yogi Berra and Yogi Bear are not the same entity. From watching Ken Burns documentaries of Baseball yearly to going to all the games, this is a serious passion. The dream of a sandlot team has always been there. So to see how this team has fallen into place is beautiful. It’s cool to have the opportunity to drive down to Austin and experience The Long Time field with the Texas Playboys playing. You can feel the love put into this sandlot commune of this place, everything is designed with purpose and nostalgia for the sport. You don’t have to love sports to appreciate this, because there’s magic here. I really enjoy talking to everyone on this team… each person is an interesting conversation. Reminds me of Bad News Bears. What a fun 24 hours. 

#baseball #sandlot #sandlotbaseball #thelongtimetexas #austin #texasplayboysbaseball @thelongtimetexas @texasplayboysbaseball  @huntervondoom

Black is such a happy color 🦨

The last few weeks have all been about Ladylove and I was going through mental stress over it. Grabbed the hair dye one morning when my roots were coming in, and tried to get it back to its natural color. Thought it would ground me. It’s not suppose to be this dark, but damn close. It’s is the color of my eyebrows. It’s been red for so long, dying it red since high school, So this has been weird. Feeling very Morticia Adams… especially with home many black dresses I own. Not used to seeing my reflection. Maybe I’ll keep it, maybe I’ll go back. Idk. Nothing is permanent in life.

“Every time I think of you
I feel shot right through with a bolt of blue
It's no problem of mine, but it's a problem I find
Livin' a life that I can't leave behind
There's no sense in telling me
The wisdom of the fool won't set you free
But that's the way that it goes and it's what nobody knows
Well, every day my confusion grows” - New Order 

I’ve been busy and tired, however any time I’ve seen my friends it’s been so wonderful and uplifting. I try to fill my time with people because that’s where I’m the happiest, on adventures with people I enjoy. Conversations. Dinner parties. Playing pool.

As we get closer to opening @ladylovedallas, it’s sinking in that this is happening. It’s my life. It’s our baby. It’s a lot of magic in a constant experience of learning. I’m terrified and excited all at once… if you know me personally you know I’ll run head first into things with the most ridiculous confidence. I go with my gut, and so far my guts treated me right. My gut feels good about this place. I wanted to thank everyone who has shown up for our private events. It’s been special to see friends and family enjoying this extended audiophile’s delight. @negronimisses has made a killer cocktail list, @42wineco is the mastermind behind the kitchen & food… Jimmy really is The Godfather of Bishop Arts. David is the reason this place exists, he’s worked every moment he’s been awake… he really is the hardest worker I know. The sound quality is thanks to David’s passion for quality music. Our bar staff is fucking awesome, they really have the best energy and I’m honored they are at our record lounge. Anyways. I’m overwhelmed with emotions. @spinsterrecords girls have been supporting each other through it all. I love my family. I love these people. I’m a lucky girl. 🪩✨ We open July 7th

#polaroid #poloroid #bishoparts #bishopartsdistrict #dj

Props to my mom for all these cute outfits when I was a little peanut. The 90s were an awesome childhood. I hope to have kids someday because it’s just in me to do that. Idk. Sometimes I’ll get nostalgic, and remember how wonderful my childhood was, and I’d like to do that again. Omg, and the cute little outfits…. Someday. 😂 Got gushy over these photos from my mom yesterday. I was a cutie… don’t know what happened.

The best advice I can give anyone about their 20s is to be selfish. Go to parties, have many lovers, try new things, work weird jobs to survive, jump on a plane alone, let people kindly go when it’s time to part ways, dress up all crazy, try to live alone at least once, and enjoy yourself. I’m not wise at 30 by any means, but looking back on the last decade I can’t think of any regrets. I went with my gut a lot. Even the things that brought me pain were worth it in strange ways. I’ve found this massive relief when I turned 30 in March… like, I got this. 30s will be even better. You know who you are. I can now age into some old witch 😂 Anyways. Went through some pictures today, and these are memories over the last decade that bring me joy or have a story behind them. I don’t want to see young people hold on to fear of experimenting. You only get one spin.

✨It’s Magic✨

We are finally open at @ladylovedallas 🪩 David and I talked about having our own music space for years now… and when we signed the lease in September 2022 we didn’t know what to expect. We are both record shop DJs, and not Bartenders. The vision was always there to build the dream DJ booth that DJs would love… so often we have spun at places where the sound quality was awful or we got a shaky table to put our gear on. We wanted high quality audio for our fellow vinyl nerds. The interior was designed by Andra Maldovan at Keeton Interiors… she’s a powerhouse. I hand picked out the artwork with Heather, our Bar Manager, and we tried our best to capture femininity in all forms. We also second handed a lot of the art from Dallas spots such as Lula B’s, East Dallas Vintage, Benny Jacks, and Dolly Python. I love antique shops. Julie McCullough of Harkensbeck did the curtains and also contributed to the artwork. The amount of strong femme energy put into this room is one of the reasons I love it so dearly. It’s an ode to lady and love. It’s magical to make an empty room into its own entity. 

#ladylove #ladylovelounge #dallas #vintage #disco #bishoparts #bishopartsdistrict #oakcliff #dj #djbooth

How it’s been going… 🥃

@ladylovedallas opening has been a success. The energy is great. I love our staff, and I can’t wait to see what’s to come. We are still learning, making mistakes, and adjusting hours till it’s just right. It’s all been a wild learning process, and it’s a lot to take in. I’m expecting an entire range of emotion. Everything that could go wrong will go wrong.
 I’ve been drinking mocktails the last week… I never like to say “I quit drinking” because surely I’ll have another soon… but I really wanted this first week to have no numbing agent. I wanted to feel it all. Good and Bad. I wanted to be focused and astute. I wanted it all to be sobering despite being a bar 😂 All in all, I’m thankful to everyone who has come out and I really love Ladylove. David, Jimmy, Heather, and I make a really good time and I’m honored to be in this with them. 

#ladylove #vinyl #dj #turntables #recordlounge #bishoparts #oakcliff

The other day I bought Van Morrison “Astral Weeks”. I like to give credit when credit is due and @aintnolobos showed me this album a decade ago when I was 20. So thank you. Anyways, this album can uplift your spirits when you need to soothe your sorrows. The song “Sweet Thing” kills me inside. The lyrics are so sad, but optimistic. I always thought it sounded like not being with the love of your life and learning to move forward. Keeping them on this pedestal at a distance since after all they’re your sweet thing. Jeff Buckleys cover of the song gives me goosebumps… also he somehow turned this short song into 10 minutes long with moans and guitar rifts. A very Jeff Buckley thing to do. Either way, I’m happy to now own it to listen to on days I feel sad. My favorite thing about music is it doesn’t disagree with you, it’s just there to relate to. I think that’s why we need it. 

#vanmorrison #sweetthing #vinyl #records #recordshop #vinylcollection #vinylcommunity #spinsterrecords

Fuck. Where do I even begin with this birthday girl. Paula is one of my most favorite people on the planet. She’s resilient, empathetic, dreamy, sensitive, creative, hilarious, and is such a character she could never be replaced or even compared. She’s my best friend. I love her. If anyone fucks with Paula they fuck with me, and I’ve had that feeling since the moment I met her at SingleWide November 2020. My favorite thing about Paula is she likes animals more than humans, she goes home at 11pm from parties because she loves her bed more than drunk people, She will watch Rock of Love with me while painting birdhouses, She calls people out of their bullshit, we daydream about being witches in that house from practical magic, she’s an encyclopedia of classic rock music. 🦀 She’s my crabby lady. Honestly, the world felt less lonely the moment I met Paula. If I had one wish it would be to bring Bon Scott back from the dead for her birthday. Thanks for being in my life and Happy Birthday 🦊

My mom and I were grabbing drinks and I looked down at her hands seeing my own in 30 years. We laugh the same, and dance to the same song. I’m definitely her daughter down to mannerisms. Anytime the world feels lonely I give her a call because she gets me. 
Time slips so quickly, and everything we do with ourselves is an investment of time. Where we put our love, ambition, attention, plans, labels… I think so much of my anxiety and fear is spent being curious if I’m happy, and will I be happy in 5 or 10 years with what I’m doing in these moments? I want to look back, and know I’m living this life fully… I don’t do anything half assed. I gave friends opportunities to grow or be in their element. So much of wanting to do Ladylove was to create a space for music where people connected and felt welcomed. I want my personal home to be refuge for friends if they need somewhere to go. I want the people I love to know their loved. When I love someone it doesn’t go away… it’s an everlasting thing with seasons. I don’t think people are meant to be together forever, but I don’t know shit and maybe the universe will surprise me someday. Just because something might not work now, it doesn’t mean it won’t work later. When you seem like you have it all, you can feel like you have nothing. So for happiness I’m pushing myself on enjoying the details… not being so stressed about the big picture; When am I having kids? or getting married or making that big move I always obsessed over? I don’t want to stress over these things I do dream of someday and that have pressure applied when entering my 30s. It’s been destroying me. I need to take in the small moments. Enjoy the conversations in between the chaos of life. Dance under moonlight. Learn what being alone is. Sing The Cramps music in my car with my mom.

And six months ago, when Doug introduced me to you guys, I thought, "Wait a second, could it be?" And now I know for sure, I just added two more girls to my wolf pack. Four of us wolves, running around the swamp together, in New Orleans, looking for strippers and cocaine. So tonight, I make a toast! 🍻🔪🩸

A few months ago I noticed my hands shaking and my heart had a sharp pain in it. It was on a day I was working a double with so many other things to do as well. One of my friends noticed my hands and said “You probably have anxiety”. 
I think I do despite having been in denial of it. I sometimes assume I’m so confident that anxiety would never cross my path. I want to seem fearless. 

It’s hard to keep it together… especially when it feels overwhelming. I have always thought handling multiple stressful situations with grace and humor is my strong suit, but I’d lie to say my body agrees with these forced actions. There’s so many times I bite off more than I can chew, and find myself sitting in my car after work trying to find my breath after pushing through. Trying to exist in multiple places at once is exhausting. Trying to be someone to anyone is exhausting. Being in jobs where people are your focus, and knowing you have to talk to people every day is exhausting. 

There’s a lot of days I fantasize about being alone in the woods at some cabin far away from everything. It’s not that I’m doing what I don’t love, I’m grateful… I just crave simplicity when things have become a lot. I think with how Instagram is and what I share with people I don’t know well… I often seem like I’m floating along living the dream and socializing a bunch when actually I feel misunderstood a lot, depressed, and uncertain of myself. There’s days I don’t want to leave my bed. No one is always happy, and life gives no promises of satisfaction. I think just because someone is good at hiding their anxiety, it doesn’t mean it doesn’t exist. I think many people feel this way… and I guess I’m writing this to say I relate if you do too. It sucks.

I was thinking about this today when I was noticing how many viral songs used on TikTok, Netflix, Instagram are resurrected from the dead. Songs that never hit full potential of acknowledgment from the masses in the time it was made. It’s not exactly that art is created for that sole purpose, however I know many artists who struggle with creating art that is forgotten, ignored, or misunderstood. It can feel defeating to create something and experience no acknowledgment for your efforts and vulnerability. I think whatever you make will exist infinitely, and will eventually move or strike someone. Hell, it could potentially hit a mass market after you die… which is so common for the majority of “Great” artists in history. The idea that the art you make outlives you is a beautiful thing, and I hope that gives people confidence to make things. To really pour their heart out. To never expect anything. To know the potential of a legacy. You will never know your true reach in this short life. Anyways! Have a nice day. Art knows no mortality 💀

#rant #music #vinyl #artists #art #tiktok #musicians #artistsoninstagram

It’s been only two months into Ladylove being open… mentally it feels like a year. We signed our lease & started this entire thing in September 2022. It was somewhat on a whim of a record shop dream David and I would brainstorm about… I didn’t tell my parents or anyone that I was doing it… I actually kept it a secret for two weeks straight 😂 I don’t know why, but until construction begun, a logo was made, and the concept was fully drawn out I was so scared of it being sabotaged by universal forces from speaking about it. Knock on wood. 
These past two months have felt long… it feels like I’ve met more people now than in the past 3 years. This is the most independent and decisive I’ve ever felt. My personal life has changed dramatically, but I’m adjusting. I love telling people “no” because I’ve hit an age where there’s no guilt with that. I cherish rest despite always being tired. It’s not easy, and if it wasn’t for Jimmy, Heather, and David it wouldn’t exists as it does. We are 4 cogs in this little machine. I love them so much. I’m just thankful for it all happening and flowing. If you haven’t stopped by, please do. Not every night is loud and packed with a line. We have mellow week days that I personally enjoy the most. Conversation cocktail nights. 

📸 @mrhuggins

Anytime people can’t decide between things I always think “why not both”. Surely you can eat the whole cake sometimes. You can be free and reserved, taste caviar in overalls, work in multiple worlds, drive to where you want to be if only for a sleepless night. If it isn’t harming anyone, do as you please. I rather be tired juggling it all than unsatisfied with life.

Whenever we were opening Ladylove I was quietly freaking out. There was an imposter syndrome behind the experience that still lingers. 
There was this one morning where I didn’t feel like myself at all so I grabbed a box of dark brown hair dye and just coated my head. I showed up to the bartender training with black dye still on my ears unrecognizable to staff. Someone joked that Halloween came early. I felt out of my vessel. 
I’ve always been the redhead at Spinster Records, and I felt such a need for escape from a multitude of things around me… relationships, family, work, my home, the internet… that I thought I would solve this issue by dying my hair and trying to hold my ground. A fight over flight. I stopped posting videos on TikTok when the bar started since I felt so unlike myself… trying to figure out my role in things. I wasn’t getting inspired rants to talk about online like I did in the record shop. Which made me sad, but I won’t do online stuff unless it’s true and full. 
Despite the chaos, the bar opening was the push I needed for change… I needed this bar and transition more than I thought. Something about the entire experience gave me courage to tell people “no” more often. To not sacrifice my own happiness to please others and their comforts. To take more pride in myself and not let someone tell me who I am. I feel the strongest I’ve ever felt… liberated and determined. I feel vulnerable to people who deserve it. I feel things fall more and more into place every day. I dyed my hair back to red yesterday thanks to @michaelalanbrunnerhair and felt like I earned the dynamite back. I got my red back. I got that burn and fire inside me that sparked the initial ambition of the projects existing now. I’m in my bones. I’m eating sex cookies. I’m existing in the spaces I want to with people who inspire me. And fuck… I am happy. 

Also wanted to mention that @theoscarlozada is one of the better photographers in Dallas and he’s captured Ladylove in a way that makes it cinematic. Bravo.

A lot can be said in a stare and a nod…

My only advice for all DJs when they’re in control of their audio 🧡
It’s the main thing I’ve noticed during DJ sets and shows anywhere in any city… Louder doesn’t always mean better. The point of a show isn’t to blow the ear drums out of the audience. If the audio system is high quality, and the room is designed right for the sound you don’t need to blast it to be heard. I think a lot of DJs miss the mark with the audience by not reading the room and turning it up way too loud. No one remembers a show for being good because it was loud. Anyways. Just thought it was worth mentioning since it’s the one thing that I’ve seen quickly ruin a set for really talented folks for a few years now. The audience isn’t stepping outside because the music sucks, a lot of the time it’s because it’s too loud. 🙉 Anyways. Love you all. Really love all the DJ sets I’ve been getting to witness, and excited for the next few months of bookings.

I’ve been so busy lately I hardly have time to ever post anything on my personal page with extra thought like I used to. This profile has become a constant photo dump as if Instagram is my forever scrapbook. I feel in my skin & have love boiling in my bones. I’m in love in a way that makes me feel so tender about life. Booking at Ladylove has been magic 🪄It’s been so cool to meet so many DJs, and curate a sound being brought into a space for folks to dance to. I love running the social media and marketing. It’s all grassroots and it is a small business… so it runs that way. There’s nights I’ll look around and get imposter syndrome. Still in disbelief I’m a part of this magic. 

I don’t think you ever really know you’re in a scene of anything until it’s over... Beauty Bar, Cedar Social, Crown & Harp, That That, Lizard Lounge, Blow Up… were all spots in Dallas that had magic within my time existing in the city, and I felt it when there. The pulse. The sound. The characters. My fake ID sneaking me in to experience all I could. Now Ladylove is our spot, and I’ll never know what it really is until it’s dead, and that’s a freaky thought. I’m enjoying this pulse, while trying to balance and embrace all the other special things in my life. I feel it’s special… maybe because it’s the baby of Heather, David, Jimmy, and myself… but my gut feels good about it existing. Like it fell into place at the right time. Like all good things do.

We whisper weird things into each other’s ear to make the other person laugh in awkward quiet situations… and that’s why I’m always smiling. 

He gets it, and I love how his brain works. So observant, so particular, never scared to rock the boat a little when things are bland or someone is in the wrong. We are so much the same… I’m less hairy and don’t wear cowboy boots as often, but we have similar hearts. I love staring at his handsome face and his smile makes me melt… I’m pretty weak for the mischievous smile. When I’m hurt he says “who do I need to beat up” and it just makes me giggle… he’s always ready for war and I think it’s amusing. I feel most like myself when I’m with him, and just wanted to post all this because I appreciate having someone in my life who makes me feel understood and loved. You can spend years in crowded rooms and feel very lonely & misunderstood, but I don’t ever feel that with Jason even when we are miles apart. It’s refreshing and I love how these feelings caught me off guard. 😂 Gushy post I know, I’m not usually like this…. Lemme have my damn cake. @abstract_reality
